3aed361e-ca17-4c9e-b7df-8b23053a27a1	fb6dca89-1d69-4097-8e70-9c77d6710a6a	WRQ-CUST-CF9A	[{"order": 1, "title": "Access CMS or Codebase for Homepage", "description": "Log into the CMS (e.g., Sanity, WordPress, or equivalent) or access the project repository to locate the homepage configuration. Identify whether the meta description is managed via a CMS field, a Head component, or a static HTML/config file.", "estimated_hours": 0.25}, {"order": 2, "title": "Locate Existing Homepage Meta Description", "description": "Find the current meta description tag for the homepage. This may be in a <head> section of index.html, a Next.js/Gatsby Head component, a CMS SEO settings panel, or a metadata configuration file such as next.config.js or a dedicated SEO schema.", "estimated_hours": 0.25}, {"order": 3, "title": "Update Meta Description with Provided Copy", "description": "Replace the existing meta description value with the approved copy: 'WebriQ Central Hub is your all-in-one digital workspace for managing web projects, content, and teams — built for speed, collaboration, and modern web standards.' Ensure no trailing whitespace or encoding issues are introduced.", "estimated_hours": 0.25}, {"order": 4, "title": "Verify Character Length and SEO Compliance", "description": "Confirm the updated meta description is within the recommended 150–160 character range. Validate that the content is unique, does not contain special character encoding issues, and meets standard SEO best practices. Use a character counter to confirm length is compliant.", "estimated_hours": 0.25}, {"order": 5, "title": "Commit Changes to Version Control", "description": "Stage and commit the updated file(s) to the appropriate branch in the version control system (e.g., Git). Use a clear commit message such as 'feat(seo): update homepage meta description for improved CTR'.", "estimated_hours": 0.25}, {"order": 6, "title": "Create and Submit Pull Request for Review", "description": "Open a pull request (PR) targeting the main or production branch. Include a brief description of the change, referencing the task ID from Zoho Projects. Request a peer review if required by team workflow.", "estimated_hours": 0.25}, {"order": 7, "title": "Deploy Changes to Production", "description": "Once the PR is approved and merged, trigger the deployment pipeline (CI/CD) to push the changes to the production environment. Follow the standard deployment process as no staging constraints have been specified.", "estimated_hours": 0.5}, {"order": 8, "title": "Validate Meta Description Rendering in Browser", "description": "After deployment, open the homepage in a browser and inspect the page source (Ctrl+U or Developer Tools > Elements) to confirm the updated meta description tag is correctly rendered in the <head> section.", "estimated_hours": 0.25}, {"order": 9, "title": "Validate Using SEO Meta Preview Tools", "description": "Use tools such as Google Search Console, Screaming Frog, or an online meta tag preview utility to verify the meta description appears correctly and renders as expected in search result snippets.", "estimated_hours": 0.25}, {"order": 10, "title": "Request Google Recrawl via Search Console", "description": "Log into Google Search Console, navigate to the URL Inspection tool, enter the homepage URL, and request a re-index to prompt Google to pick up the updated meta description promptly.", "estimated_hours": 0.25}, {"order": 11, "title": "Document Change and Notify Stakeholder", "description": "Update the Zoho Projects task with a completion note summarizing what was changed, the file(s) affected, and confirmation that the update is live. Notify the requester (Test WebriQ) via formal communication in line with the customer's preferred tone.", "estimated_hours": 0.25}]	["pages/index.html", "pages/index.js", "app/page.tsx", "components/Head.js", "components/SEO.js", "next.config.js", "gatsby-config.js", "sanity/schema/seo.js", "public/index.html"]	["Google Search Console (URL Inspection / Request Indexing API)", "CMS API (if meta description is managed via headless CMS such as Sanity or Contentful)"]	["SEO Metadata Update Playbook", "CMS Content Update Playbook", "Standard Deployment and QA Playbook"]	88.00	["CMS platform and tech stack for StackShift are not explicitly specified — affected file paths are assumed and must be confirmed upon access", "It is unknown whether the meta description is managed via a CMS GUI or directly in the codebase, which may affect the update approach", "No staging environment requirement was specified; if one exists, the deployment step should be adjusted accordingly", "Open Graph (og:description) and Twitter Card meta tags may also need to be updated to maintain consistency across social sharing previews — this was not addressed in the original request"]	PENDING_APPROVAL	\N	\N	\N	claude-sonnet-4-6	1163	1104	2026-06-02 12:34:31.752373+00	2026-06-02 12:34:31.752373+00	\N	f
535c74f6-8841-4dd5-85c5-334c29af0b85	fb6dca89-1d69-4097-8e70-9c77d6710a6a	WRQ-CUST-CF9A	[{"order": 1, "title": "Identify Homepage Meta Description Location", "description": "Access the CMS (e.g., StackShift CMS) or codebase repository for the Test Central Hub StackShift product. Locate the homepage meta description field — this may be in a CMS SEO settings panel, a Head component, a layout file, or a metadata configuration file. Document the current meta description value before making any changes.", "estimated_hours": 0.5}, {"order": 2, "title": "Backup Current Meta Description Value", "description": "Record the existing homepage meta description in the task notes or a change log entry for audit and rollback purposes. This ensures the previous value can be restored if needed.", "estimated_hours": 0.25}, {"order": 3, "title": "Update Meta Description with Provided Copy", "description": "Replace the existing meta description with the approved copy: 'WebriQ Central Hub is your all-in-one digital workspace for managing web projects, content, and teams — built for speed, collaboration, and modern web standards.' Ensure the em dash (—) and special characters are rendered correctly and are not escaped or malformed in the output HTML.", "estimated_hours": 0.5}, {"order": 4, "title": "Verify Character Length and SEO Compliance", "description": "Confirm the updated meta description is within the recommended 150–160 character range. Validate that no truncation is required. Also confirm that the description does not contain duplicate keywords, spammy patterns, or formatting that could violate search engine guidelines.", "estimated_hours": 0.25}, {"order": 5, "title": "Inspect Meta Tag Rendering in Codebase or CMS Preview", "description": "Review the rendered HTML to confirm the meta description tag appears correctly in the <head> section as: <meta name='description' content='WebriQ Central Hub is your all-in-one digital workspace for managing web projects, content, and teams — built for speed, collaboration, and modern web standards.' />. Check for proper attribute quoting and no HTML entity issues.", "estimated_hours": 0.25}, {"order": 6, "title": "Deploy Changes to Staging (If Applicable)", "description": "If a staging or preview environment is available, deploy the change there first and validate that the meta description renders correctly in the page source before promoting to production.", "estimated_hours": 0.5}, {"order": 7, "title": "Deploy Changes to Production", "description": "Merge or publish the updated meta description to the production environment following the standard deployment process for the StackShift product. Confirm no build errors or deployment failures occur.", "estimated_hours": 0.5}, {"order": 8, "title": "Verify Live Meta Description in Production", "description": "After deployment, view the production homepage source (Ctrl+U or equivalent) and confirm the updated meta description is present and correct. Use a browser or online meta tag checker tool to validate rendering.", "estimated_hours": 0.25}, {"order": 9, "title": "Test with SEO Preview and Search Console Tools", "description": "Use tools such as Google Search Console, Screaming Frog, or an online SERP snippet preview tool to confirm the meta description displays correctly in search result previews. Request indexing of the homepage in Google Search Console if desired to accelerate cache refresh.", "estimated_hours": 0.5}, {"order": 10, "title": "Document Change and Notify Stakeholder", "description": "Update the Zoho Projects task with completion notes, including the before/after meta description values, deployment timestamp, and any tool validation screenshots. Notify the requester (Test WebriQ, test.webriq@gmail.com) in a formal communication confirming the update is live.", "estimated_hours": 0.25}]	["pages/index.js", "pages/_document.js", "components/Head.js", "components/SEO.js", "layouts/default.js", "public/index.html", "next.config.js", "seo.config.js", "cms-config/homepage-seo-settings.json"]	["Google Search Console API", "StackShift CMS Content API"]	["SEO Meta Tag Update Playbook", "CMS Content Update Playbook", "Production Deployment Playbook", "QA Validation and Sign-Off Playbook"]	91.00	["CMS vs. codebase location of meta description is unconfirmed — implementation path may differ depending on whether the homepage SEO fields are managed in the StackShift CMS UI or hardcoded in the repository source files.", "Special characters (em dash —) must be verified to render correctly in HTML output and not be inadvertently escaped or stripped by the CMS or build pipeline.", "No staging environment requirements were specified; if one exists, it should be used prior to production deployment to reduce risk.", "Google Search Console cache refresh may take days to reflect the updated meta description in live search results, which could affect stakeholder expectations on visibility timing."]	APPROVED	\N	\N	ec2e272c-7049-4790-b376-5454a3773f4d	claude-sonnet-4-6	1163	1097	2026-06-02 12:34:45.730571+00	2026-06-03 05:08:26.355157+00	\N	f
