tudio", "description": "Once preview review is satisfactory, publish the updated hero section document in Sanity Studio. Record the Sanity document ID for reference in the Zoho task closure comment.", "estimated_hours": 0.25}, {"order": 14, "title": "Verify Changes on Live Production URL", "description": "Within 5 minutes of publishing, load the live production URL for the updated page and confirm the hero section reflects all changes. Allow up to 10 minutes for full CDN propagation as per the Content Update Playbook acceptance criteria.", "estimated_hours": 0.25}, {"order": 15, "title": "Cross-Browser and Responsive QA Review", "description": "Test the updated hero section across major browsers (Chrome, Firefox, Safari, Edge) and key device breakpoints (desktop, tablet, mobile). Confirm no layout regressions, missing assets, or console errors are present.", "estimated_hours": 1}, {"order": 16, "title": "Accessibility and Console Error Check", "description": "Verify there are no JavaScript console errors on the updated page. Confirm image alt-text is present, colour contrast meets WCAG AA standards, and CTA button is keyboard-navigable.", "estimated_hours": 0.5}, {"order": 17, "title": "Client Review and Sign-Off", "description": "Share the live production URL with the Test Central Hub client contact for formal review and written sign-off. Document approval in Zoho Projects.", "estimated_hours": 0.25}, {"order": 18, "title": "Close Zoho Task with Change Summary", "description": "Add a formal closing comment to Zoho Projects task WRQ-CUST-CF9A including the Sanity document ID, a summary of all changes made, the live URL, and the date/time of publish. Mark the task as complete.", "estimated_hours": 0.25}]	["Sanity CMS hero section document (document ID to be confirmed)", "Hero image/video/background asset files (to be supplied by client)", "Sanity schema file for hero section (if field-level changes are required)"]	["Sanity Content Lake API", "Sanity Asset Pipeline / 