ource", "description": "Using browser DevTools or a view-source inspection, confirm that the <title> tag in the HTML head outputs the correct new value. Additionally verify that any structured metadata or JSON-LD on the Home page does not still reference the old brand name 'Medusa Template'.", "estimated_hours": 0.25}, {"order": 7, "title": "Commit Changes and Submit Pull Request", "description": "Stage and commit the updated file(s) with a clear commit message such as 'SEO: Update Home page title to Shop with Confidence and Elegance | LUXORA'. Open a pull request targeting the appropriate branch (e.g., main or develop) for review.", "estimated_hours": 0.25}, {"order": 8, "title": "Deploy to Staging Environment", "description": "Merge the approved pull request or deploy the branch to the staging environment. Confirm the updated title is live on the staging Home page by inspecting the rendered HTML and browser tab title.", "estimated_hours": 0.25}, {"order": 9, "title": "Client Review and Sign-Off on Staging", "description": "Notify the Test WebriQ team of the staging deployment and request formal sign-off on the updated Home page title before promoting to production.", "estimated_hours": 0.25}, {"order": 10, "title": "Deploy to Production", "description": "Upon client approval, deploy the changes to the production environment via the established deployment pipeline. Confirm the Home page title reads 'Shop with Confidence and Elegance | LUXORA' in the live environment.", "estimated_hours": 0.25}]	["pages/index.js", "pages/index.tsx", "app/page.tsx", "app/page.js", "src/pages/index.js", "src/pages/index.tsx", "components/Layout.js", "components/Head.js", "_document.js", "next.config.js", "gatsby-config.js", "nuxt.config.js", "public/index.html"]	[]	["SEO Metadata Update Playbook", "Standard Code Review and PR Workflow", "Staging and Production Deployment Checklist"]	92.00	["The exact file path containing the title tag is unknown until the codebase is inspected — frame