cifications. If customer cannot provide, flag for copywriting or placeholder values pending approval.", "estimated_hours": 0.5}, {"order": 6, "title": "Pull Latest Content and Codebase from Target Platform", "description": "Pull the latest content from Sanity CMS (if applicable) for the target dataset, and/or pull the latest codebase from the relevant repository for the identified product. Ensure local or staging environment is up to date before making changes.", "estimated_hours": 0.5}, {"order": 7, "title": "Create the New Homepage Document or Page Entry", "description": "In the target platform's CMS (Sanity Studio or equivalent), create a new page document using the confirmed slug and template. If code-based, create the appropriate page file in the project repository (e.g., index file or route-based page component).", "estimated_hours": 1}, {"order": 8, "title": "Apply Page Template and Scaffold Structure", "description": "Apply the agreed-upon template or layout structure to the new page. If 'blank' was confirmed to mean no content, leave content regions empty but ensure the page shell, header, and footer components are correctly wired. If scaffolded, add placeholder sections as approved.", "estimated_hours": 1.5}, {"order": 9, "title": "Populate SEO Metadata Fields", "description": "Enter the confirmed SEO metadata (title tag, meta description, OG tags, canonical URL) into the CMS or page configuration. Verify metadata fields render correctly in the page head on preview.", "estimated_hours": 0.5}, {"order": 10, "title": "Configure Navigation Entry (If Required)", "description": "Update the site navigation configuration to include or replace the homepage entry as agreed. This may involve editing a navigation schema in Sanity, a nav config file in the repository, or a CMS navigation document.", "estimated_hours": 1}, {"order": 11, "title": "Preview Changes in Staging Environment", "description": "Deploy or preview the new page in the staging or preview environment. Use the Sanity Preview URL if applicable. Verify the page loads at the correct URL, the template renders correctly, and no console errors are present.", "estimated_hours": 1}, {"order": 12, "title": "Conduct Cross-Browser and Responsive QA", "description": "Test the new homepage across major browsers (Chrome, Firefox, Safari, Edge) and at key responsive breakpoints (mobile, tablet, desktop) to ensure the blank/scaffolded layout renders correctly without visual regressions.", "estimated_hours": 1.5}, {"order": 13, "title": "Validate SEO Metadata on Preview", "description": "Use browser developer tools or an SEO inspection tool to confirm that the title tag, meta description, and OG tags are correctly rendered in the page head on the staging/preview URL.", "estimated_hours": 0.5}, {"order": 14, "title": "Internal Review and PM Sign-Off", "description": "Share the staging/preview URL with the PM for internal review and approval before publishing to production. Document any requested changes and apply them before proceeding.", "estimated_hours": 1}, {"order": 15, "title": "Publish Page to Production", "description": "Once internal sign-off is received, publish the new homepage document in Sanity Studio or deploy the code change to production. Follow the Content Update Playbook publish process to ensure correct propagation.", "estimated_hours": 0.5}, {"order": 16, "title": "Verify Live Page on Production URL", "description": "Within 5 minutes of publishing, verify the new homepage is accessible on the production URL, renders correctly, and displays no console errors. Confirm CDN propagation is complete within the 10-minute acceptance window.", "estimated_hours": 0.5}, {"order": 17, "title": "Validate Navigation and Internal Linking", "description": "Confirm that any navigation links pointing to the homepage resolve correctly on production and that no broken internal links were introduced by adding or replacing the homepage.", "estimated_hours": 0.5}, {"order": 18, "ti